added.title: The Signature
added.description: Dad discovers that Granny Jojo and Louie are planning to get married and move to Florida. To stop this happening he adopts Louie so that he can forbid him from marrying Granny Jojo. But this triggers a series of adoptions within the family which quickly spirals out of control, and causes the unexpected return of someone from Dad's past.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Joy
added.description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Name
added.description: When Gumball discovers his real name is Zach...he starts acting like one! When Mom reveals that Gumball's real name is "Zach", Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name.  His family try to make him remember the old Gumball, as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories. If they can't reach him in time, the old Gumball will disappear forever and they'll be left with...Zach!

added.title: The Fraud
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover Principal Brown's diploma is a fake. When Gumball and Darwin discover his diploma is fake, Principal Brown is determined to keep their discovery a secret. He offers them all sorts of "incentives" to keep quiet but the truth is they really don't care whether the diploma is real or not. Mistaking their disinterest as "playing hard to get" Principal Brown resorts to increasingly desperate measures to ensure Gumball and Darin play ball.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Watch
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

added.title: The Bumpkin
added.description: Envious of his rustic lifestyle, Gumball invites Idaho over to teach the Wattersons how to live like a potato.

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Storm
added.description: Love is in the air and Gumball is caught in the center of an emotional hurricane - literally!

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The Party
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are invited to a high school party, and have to bring a date!

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Onion Gang
added.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

added.title: Steven's Dream
added.description: A strange dream prompts Steven to search for answers.

added.title: Adventures in Light Distortion
added.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

added.title: Log Date 7 15 2
added.description: Steven sneaks a listen to a friend's audio diary.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: The New Lars
added.description: Steven gets a new look into Lars' life.

added.title: Monster Reunion
added.description: Steven reunites with an old friend.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: Mirror Gem
added.description: Steven befriends a magical mirror that can mysteriously communicate with him.

added.title: Fusion Cuisine
added.description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.

added.title: Watermelon Steven
added.description: Steven discovers a new power when he grows a patch of Steven-shaped watermelons!

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: Horror Club
added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Musclecup
added.description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

added.title: Imagine That
added.description: The Girls have to battle Him after he causes Bubbles' imagination to run wild.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
added.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Something's a Ms./Slumbering with the Enemy
added.description: Something's a Ms: Miss Bellum is acting very strange lately. And she keeps showing up at crime scenes. Has our favorite secretary gone to the dark side, or is there another woman involved here?/Slumbering With The Enemy: When the girls decide to have an all-girl slumber party, a villain decides to crash it. To what lengths will this villain go to keep his identity hidden?

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
added.description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: The Dome Experiment
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he was right about the date of the Dome Experiment.

added.title: Brilliant Century Duck Crisis Special
added.description: The park guys want to get rid of a very large bird in the park.

added.title: Paint Job
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to paint a house.

added.title: Skips Stress
added.description: Skips has to lower his stress before it kills him.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: Rage Against the TV
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try to get good at an arcade game at the coffee shop to earn some respect.

added.title: Brain Eraser
added.description: Benson gets demoted and has to work with Mordecai and Rigby.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Chess Master Steve
added.description: Pizza Steve goes to great lengths in order to beat Mr. Gus at a game of chess.

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

removed.description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.
